Explanation:
- **Spotify** is highly recommended due to its vast music catalog, good playlist features, shuffle mode, and social and collaborative playlist options. It has both free (with ads and shuffle limitations) and subscription plans, making it accessible to many users[1][3][4].
- **Amazon Music**, **Apple Music**, and **YouTube Music** are major streaming services with large catalogs and solid shuffle playlist support, usually subscription-based but with some free-tier options as well[1][3].
- **Deezer** and **SoundCloud** are well-known for their free and paid tiers and shuffle features on playlists[1][3].
- Other services like **Pandora**, **Tidal**, **iHeartRadio**, **Napster**, **Qobuz**, **Audiomack**, **Gaana**, **JioSaavn**, **Wynk Music**, **Hungama Music**, **Boomplay**, **Anghami**, and **Trebel** also support playlist shuffle mode and offer various pricing models from free to subscription-based plans[1][3].
- **TuneIn Radio** is included as a free streaming service with music and radio options, often supporting shuffle play on playlists[3].

This list prioritizes apps known for playlist functionality with shuffle mode, broad music catalogs, and a mix of free and paid options, aligning with your cost-based ranking criterion.